    {
      "id": "github-repo-smoke-intro",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "GitHub Repo Node Smoke",
      "position": {
        "x": -700,
        "y": -720
      },
      "width": 760,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# GitHub Repo Node Smoke Test\n\nGoal: prove the first-pass `github-repo` class is usable as a real authored primitive.\n\nWhat this graph tests:\n- the class resolves through a visible import bridge\n- a known-good `github-repo` instance renders\n- the instance editor exposes the expected repo fields\n- the instance can switch between its detail, summary, and icon surfaces\n- a second repo node can be created from the bridge without type-resolution errors"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-repo-smoke-known",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Known Good Sample",
      "position": {
        "x": 100,
        "y": -720
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Known Good Sample\n\nThe sample repo node in this graph uses:\n\n- `owner`: `twilitellc`\n- `repo`: `public`\n- `branch`: `main`\n- `homeRef`: `/root.node`\n\nExpected interpretation:\n- repo identity is `twilitellc/public`\n- home resolution is declaration-driven when available\n- `/root.node` remains the bootstrap fallback"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-repo-smoke-step-01",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 1",
      "position": {
        "x": -980,
        "y": -360
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 1: Open The Graph\n\nAction:\n- Open this smoke test graph.\n- Confirm the sample repo node renders on canvas.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-repo-smoke-expect-01",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Expected 1",
      "position": {
        "x": -420,
        "y": -360
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "### Expected\n\n- The `GitHub Repo` card renders.\n- No `Unknown node type` error appears.\n- The sample reads as a repo identity surface, not a generic placeholder card."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-repo-smoke-step-02",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 2",
      "position": {
        "x": -980,
        "y": -100
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 2: Edit The Sample Repo Node\n\nAction:\n- Select the sample `github-repo` node.\n- Open its editor.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-repo-smoke-expect-02",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Expected 2",
      "position": {
        "x": -420,
        "y": -100
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "### Expected\n\nThe editor should expose:\n- `Title`\n- `Owner`\n- `Repo`\n- `Branch`\n- `Home Ref`\n- `Notes`\n\nNo unrelated GitHub installation or commit controls should appear in v1."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-repo-smoke-step-03",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 3",
      "position": {
        "x": -980,
        "y": 180
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 3: Change Repo Fields\n\nAction:\n- Change `branch` to something else.\n- Change `homeRef` to another plausible path.\n- Save/commit the edit in the panel.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-repo-smoke-expect-03",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Expected 3",
      "position": {
        "x": -420,
        "y": 180
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "### Expected\n\n- The node updates without crashing.\n- Branch and home-ref text update in the visible surface.\n- The node still reads as a stable repo object rather than a raw file URL."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "github-repo-smoke-step-04",
